2010, china overtook japan to become the world's second largest economy after the united states. china continues to develop economically at a breakneck speed, but what lies ahead for the middle kingdom is anybody's guess. politics[edit] china is a one-party authoritarian state tightly ruled by the communist party of china. china has actually only experienced one open nation-wide election, in 1912. the government consists of an executive branch known as the state council (国务院 guó wù yuàn), as well as a unicameral legislature known as the national people's congress (全国人民代表大会 quánguó rénmín dàibiǎo dàhuì). the head of state is the 